Tipwindow.mcc/MUIA_Tip_Show

    NAME
        MUIM_Tip_Show      v15

        DoMethod(obj, MUIM_Tip_Show, Flags );


    FUNCTION
        Shows Tip of the day. If called sequently, will show
        next tip each time. Tips never ends (when showing forward,
        1st one will be shown after last, or vice versa when showing
        tips backwards)

	FLAGS
        MUIV_Tip_Show_Startup
        MUIV_Tip_Show_Next
        MUIV_Tip_Show_Prev
        MUIV_Tip_Show_Random

    NOTE: When MUIV_Tip_Show_Next, Prev or Random are used,
          the Tip window will pop up, no matter what the state of
          "show tip on startup" is.  MUIV_Tip_Show_Startup is
          almost the same as MUIV_Tip_Show_Next, but it takes
          care of user will (stored in ".tipc" file). It's
          recommended to use this flag when you show tips on
          startup, but also to have menu item (like "Show tip of
          the day...") that will call this method with
          MUIV_Tip_Show_Next, to allow user to change his mind
          (or to read more tips w/o forcing him to restart your
          application which'd be totally lame ;-)

    EXAMPLE
		DoMethod( obj, MUIA_Tip_Show, MUIV_Tip_Show_Startup );

    SEE ALSO
		See example demo program

